
Sending a command
-----------------
1. intent to send a command received
2. intent to send a command needs to be persisted asap to intention is not lost
3. intent to send command is logged
4. command is transmitted to host on recipient
5. host persists command in recipient persists command and sends an ack to sender
6. sender marks command as being processed / removes it so not sent again
7. host on recipient forwards command to registered handler
8. register handler processes message and sends ack
9. host on recipient marks command as completed



Questions
---------
1. How will intent to send a command be received?
2. How will intent to send a command be persisted?

